title: President Biden Announces Presidential Delegation to the United Arab Emirates to Attend the United States National Day at the Expo 2020 Dubai | The White House
content: FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASEMarch 4, 2022President Biden Announces Presidential Delegation to the United Arab Emirates to Attend the United States National Day at the Expo 2020 Dubai President Joseph R. Biden, Jr. today announced the designation of a Presidential Delegation to the United Arab Emirates to attend the United States National Day at Expo 2020 Dubai on March 6, 2022.  The Honorable Gina M. Raimondo, Secretary of Commerce, will lead the delegation.Members of the Presidential Delegation:Mr. Sean Murphy, Chargé d’Affaires ad interim, U.S. Embassy Abu DhabiThe Honorable Roy Blunt, United States Senator (R), MissouriMs. Jennifer Hall Godfrey, Senior Official for Public Diplomacy and Public of Affairs, U.S. Department of StateThe Honorable Maria Rosario Jackson, Ph.D., Chair of the National Endowment for the ArtsThe Honorable Robert Clark, U.S. Commissioner General at Expo 2020 DubaiMr. Dilawar Syed, Special Representative for Commercial and Business Affairs, U.S. Department of StateThe Honorable Barbara Leaf, Special Assistant to the President and Senior Director for the Middle East and North Africa, National Security CouncilMs. Meghan Gregonis, Consul General, U.S. Consulate Dubai###
